frameDefinitions: An Entity is in a specified State.
Under some Condition, usually left implicit, a Responsible_party is required to perform some Duty.
An Entity is declared to exist, generally irrespective of its position or even the possibility of its position being specified.
A volitional  Agent is responding to a State_of_affairs by performing some Action.
Due to internal forces/properties, an Entity is inclined towards a particular Behavior, which may be to perform an action or to maintain a state.
frameExamples: Some of the classics were in excellent <t>condition</t>.
It is my <t>duty</t> to fight any attack on the Brotherhood .
Finally, Poland ceased to <t>exist</t> as a state for hundreds of years.
And was that your <t>reason</t> for becoming an actor ?
listRoleDefinitions: The entity whose <fen>State</fen> is specified and/or evaluated.
The person who must perform the <fen>Duty</fen>.
The action that the <fen>Responsible_party</fen> is obligated to perform.
The time interval during which the Responsibly_party is obligated to fulfill the Duty.
A location in which the <fen>Responsible_party</fen> has a specified <fen>Duty</fen> .
Some entity, abstract or concrete, which is stated to exist.
A time at which the entity is in existence.
The person who responds to a <fen>State_of_Affairs</fen> by performing some <fen>Action</fen>.
The action that the <fen>Agent</fen> performs in response to a <fen>State_of_Affairs</fen>.
The eventuality  that motivates the <fen>Agent</fen>'s performing a particular <fen>Action</fen> in response to it.
TheFrame Element <fen>Entity</fen> identifies the person or thing that has a tendency towards some Behaviour.
listRoleExamples: It was stressed that no diagnosis of <fex>my</fex> state of health would be made, so all she was doing was describing how she felt my 'aura' to be.
My job is <fex>to get to the other side of the bridge</fex>.
<fex>At that time</fex> men were obligated to marry women from their own community.
I almost forgot to tell you that <fex>in Sweden</fex> we are obligated to spend atleast 7.5 months in the army for training.
I find that all my reasons <fex>for postponing giving birth</fex> still apply
My reason is <fex>that our cities are now designed round the motor car</fex>
<fex>Lubomir</fex> was not inclined to believe me
